we made him confess by torturing him.

35
00:03:53,170 --> 00:03:55,440
Is there anyone else who wants to seek justice for Detective Lu?

36
00:03:58,300 --> 00:03:58,790
Take it.

37
00:03:59,620 --> 00:04:00,470
Each of us beats him once.

38
00:04:01,020 --> 00:04:01,460
Beat him!

39
00:04:02,730 --> 00:04:03,510
Beat him hard.

40
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:07,340
Three.

41
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:08,870
Four.

42
00:04:11,620 --> 00:04:12,040
Five.

43
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:41,560
Make him sign it.

44
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:03,730
My Lord.

45
00:05:05,050 --> 00:05:05,750
Lu Zheng is back.

46
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:07,910
Got it.

47
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:11,310
Xie Kengran is dead.

48
00:05:17,580 --> 00:05:19,450
Give Xie Kengran's family

49
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:21,020
a sum of settling-in allowance.

50
00:05:23,590 --> 00:05:24,040
Go.

51
00:05:32,390 --> 00:05:33,340
I killed Li Dongfang.

52
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:36,640
The Yuming Lock is still in the hands of Li Wu.

53
00:07:00,730 --> 00:07:01,700
Li Dongfang.

54
00:07:05,020 --> 00:07:05,760
You're not dead?

55
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:09,430
Right.

56
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:10,940
It's me.

57
00:07:13,460 --> 00:07:14,150
Kill me.

58
00:07:16,350 --> 00:07:17,030
Escape by yourself.

59
00:07:19,290 --> 00:07:19,680
Hurry up!

60
00:07:26,930 --> 00:07:27,650
Hang in there.

61
00:09:42,380 --> 00:09:43,060
My Lord!

62
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:43,690
My Lord!

63
00:09:46,100 --> 00:09:46,640
-My Lord. -My Lord.

64
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:47,490
Okay. Go.

65
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:49,910
Stop!

66
00:09:50,940 --> 00:09:51,780
-General Commander Cui. -Open it and let me take a look.

67
00:09:51,820 --> 00:09:52,940
What's written on the announcement?

68
00:09:53,380 --> 00:09:54,720
A rebel.

69
00:09:55,170 --> 00:09:56,690
Lu Zheng, the son of the chief commander,

70
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:57,770
is a rebel.

71
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:01,050
The world is really chaotic.

72
00:10:01,350 --> 00:10:02,470
He's a rebel?

73
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:03,860
Let's go. Stop talking about it.

74
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:16,140
[Investigation Bureau]

75
00:10:10,620 --> 00:10:12,120
Meat-packed rice.

76
00:10:12,580 --> 00:10:13,890
Vegetable-packed rice.

77
00:10:14,560 --> 00:10:15,840
Cabbage-packed rice.

78
00:10:16,420 --> 00:10:17,570
Omelet rice.

79
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:19,120
Cabbage-packed rice.

80
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:20,160
Meat-packed rice.

81
00:10:20,190 --> 00:10:21,460
And sugar-packed rice.

82
00:10:23,290 --> 00:10:23,830
Meat-packed rice.

83
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:24,920
Right away.

84
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:26,120
Have you heard about it?

85
00:10:26,580 --> 00:10:27,160
That person

86
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:29,050
might die during these few days.

87
00:10:29,460 --> 00:10:31,260
Even a high-ranking father can't do anything about it.

88
00:10:31,630 --> 00:10:32,770
He's dying soon.

89
00:10:33,110 --> 00:10:34,970
His father didn't help him.

90
00:10:35,630 --> 00:10:36,390
His father

91
00:10:36,410 --> 00:10:38,270
has been living in seclusion for days.

92
00:10:39,220 --> 00:10:41,300
Now all the affairs of the Investigation Bureau

93
00:10:41,330 --> 00:10:42,890
are decided by the deputy commander.

94
00:10:43,820 --> 00:10:44,440
Sir, it's ready.

95
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:48,120
Get lost!

96
00:10:49,260 --> 00:10:49,820
Well...

97
00:10:49,850 --> 00:10:51,140
Sir, I really can't leave now.

98
00:10:53,940 --> 00:10:54,850
I'd like to ask you something.

99
00:10:56,020 --> 00:10:57,920
Is Officer Xie Kengran here?

100
00:10:58,810 --> 00:10:59,480
He's dead.

101
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:01,540
He stinks in the courtyard now.

102
00:11:03,420 --> 00:11:04,320
Xie Kengran

103
00:11:04,940 --> 00:11:06,020
is an example of warning for you.

104
00:11:06,910 --> 00:11:07,860
He was marginalized when he was alive,

105
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:09,300
and he made a place stink after he died.

106
00:11:10,010 --> 00:11:12,010
Lu Zheng will end up like him, too.

107
00:11:14,460 --> 00:11:14,950
Just go!

108
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:37,220
You're awake.

109
00:12:40,850 --> 00:12:41,580
Are you okay?

110
00:12:54,750 --> 00:12:55,730
It was you who saved me?

111
00:13:10,090 --> 00:13:10,770
Where are you going?

112
00:13:11,220 --> 00:13:12,420
I can't let his body lie in the wilderness.

113
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:13,470
Do you know how hard I've tried

114
00:13:13,510 --> 00:13:14,390
to save you?

115
00:13:21,450 --> 00:13:22,220
Do you think I'll be grateful

116
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:23,200
just because you saved me?

117
00:13:25,170 --> 00:13:26,510
There's no gratefulness in my heart now.

118
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:28,580
There's only hatred.

119
00:13:35,130 --> 00:13:35,780
I saved you,

120
00:13:35,780 --> 00:13:36,410
and you hate me?

121
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:41,140
If I stab you to death, I'll become a good person?

122
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:43,080
What kind of nonsense is that?

123
00:13:44,030 --> 00:13:44,820
Let me tell you.

124
00:13:45,460 --> 00:13:46,130
If I kill you,

125
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:47,660
I'll only become a murderer,

126
00:13:47,710 --> 00:13:49,050
and I'll always be in panic.

127
00:14:03,450 --> 00:14:04,050
Forget it.

128
00:14:11,840 --> 00:14:12,870
Let me tell you the truth.

129
00:14:17,900 --> 00:14:18,870
He didn't want me to tell you.

130
00:14:20,350 --> 00:14:20,970
But listen carefully.

131
00:14:25,350 --> 00:14:26,150
Li Dongfang is not dead.

132
00:14:36,810 --> 00:14:38,080
I saw him...

133
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:38,970
Someone plotted against him.

134
00:14:42,140 --> 00:14:42,830
There is a traitor

135
00:14:43,380 --> 00:14:43,970
among the Night Scouts.

136
00:14:45,140 --> 00:14:46,210
He doesn't trust anyone now,

137
00:14:47,460 --> 00:14:48,220
including you.

138
00:14:52,490 --> 00:14:53,100
What do you mean?

139
00:14:55,660 --> 00:14:56,980
I'm your superior now.

140
00:14:58,620 --> 00:14:59,450
Only Li Dongfang and I

141
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:01,130
will keep in touch with each other.

142
00:15:02,580 --> 00:15:03,350
He doesn't trust me,

143
00:15:03,420 --> 00:15:04,170
but he trusts you?

144
00:15:06,130 --> 00:15:07,050
A small potato like me,

145
00:15:07,940 --> 00:15:09,630
who marks the price clearly and doesn't gang up with others,

146
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:11,580
at this moment,

147
00:15:13,490 --> 00:15:14,010
is the most trustworthy.

148
00:15:17,580 --> 00:15:18,600
Why should I trust you?

149
00:15:19,370 --> 00:15:20,200
Do you have any evidence?

150
00:15:33,530 --> 00:15:34,000
Believing it

151
00:15:34,760 --> 00:15:35,530
or not

152
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:38,000
depends on your choice.

153
00:15:41,310 --> 00:15:43,810
If you choose to believe that he's dead,

154
00:15:45,220 --> 00:15:46,020
he would be

155
00:15:46,690 --> 00:15:48,700
lying in the withered leaves of Mount Guanyin,

156
00:15:48,760 --> 00:15:49,800
rotting and stinking there.

157
00:15:53,780 --> 00:15:54,970
If you believe that he's alive,

158
00:15:56,820 --> 00:15:58,450
then he's hiding in the dark

159
00:15:59,930 --> 00:16:01,660
and looking for the traitor who plotted against him.

160
00:16:03,180 --> 00:16:04,110
If one wants to live,

161
00:16:05,430 --> 00:16:06,770
he has to choose to believe in something.

162
00:16:09,740 --> 00:16:10,410
Am I right?

163
00:16:18,630 --> 00:16:19,830
Come with me to the city to recuperate.

164
00:16:20,780 --> 00:16:22,330
I'm going to the Investigation Bureau to take up my post.

165
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:24,330
You?

166
00:16:25,660 --> 00:16:26,330
Go to take up your post?

167
00:16:37,060 --> 00:16:38,350
Actually, I should be the one

168
00:16:41,460 --> 00:16:42,540
who died on Mount Guanyin that day.

169
00:16:49,340 --> 00:16:50,840
Why did the Brocade-clad Guard Xie Kengran

170
00:16:52,510 --> 00:16:54,020
protect me from being stabbed?

171
00:16:56,850 --> 00:16:58,250
I don't understand anyway.

172
00:16:59,700 --> 00:17:00,500
For this deal,

173
00:17:03,020 --> 00:17:04,180
he sufferred loss in every aspect.

174
00:17:09,130 --> 00:17:09,990
He was an officer,

175
00:17:12,460 --> 00:17:13,579
and got seven piculs of grain every month.

176
00:17:19,550 --> 00:17:20,579
And these two stacks of cloth

177
00:17:22,180 --> 00:17:23,869
equal to his monthly salary.

178
00:17:28,060 --> 00:17:29,460
Why was he working so hard?

179
00:17:33,660 --> 00:17:34,880
His body is now

180
00:17:36,860 --> 00:17:38,880
lying in the office of the Investigation Bureau, and is stinking there.

181
00:17:41,280 --> 00:17:42,380
None of his colleagues

182
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:45,950
helps to arrange his funeral.

183
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:54,720
Why did he save me?

184
00:17:58,240 --> 00:17:59,440
Because I can save Lu Zheng?

185
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:04,970
But I'm a fraud.

186
00:18:06,510 --> 00:18:07,450
I'm a thief.

187
00:18:10,470 --> 00:18:11,820
Why did he believe me?

188
00:18:13,470 --> 00:18:15,350
I've never seen anyone like him.

189
00:18:21,650 --> 00:18:22,170
So,

190
00:18:23,540 --> 00:18:24,680
I really want to know why.

191
00:18:29,660 --> 00:18:30,350
I promised him that

192
00:18:32,640 --> 00:18:34,220
I would go to the office of Investigation Bureau to save Lu Zheng.

193
00:18:37,190 --> 00:18:38,930
I've been making a living in the society for so many years,

194
00:18:41,010 --> 00:18:42,140
and I've never owed anyone anything.

195
00:18:45,380 --> 00:18:45,910
To him,

196
00:18:51,250 --> 00:18:52,490
I have to keep my promise.

197
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:23,420
My Lord.

198
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:24,580
My Lord.

199
00:19:25,540 --> 00:19:25,890
My Lord.

200
00:19:26,290 --> 00:19:26,660
My Lord.

201
00:19:34,530 --> 00:19:36,600
I'm Detective Wang Chan. Greetings, Sergeant.

202
00:19:37,090 --> 00:19:38,750
How have you been, Detective Wang?

203
00:19:49,140 --> 00:19:49,730
Li Wu.

204
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:51,810
Do you want to die?

205
00:19:52,550 --> 00:19:53,730
How dare you fool me?

206
00:19:54,750 --> 00:19:57,430
Do you know that you'll be beheaded if you pretend to be an official and lie to an official?

207
00:19:58,850 --> 00:19:59,190
Well,

208
00:19:59,660 --> 00:20:01,060
please show mercy, My Lord.

209
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:05,210
Tell me.

210
00:20:06,140 --> 00:20:07,080
How do we put an end to this?

211
00:20:08,470 --> 00:20:10,220
Plus the money you owed me last time.

212
00:20:11,130 --> 00:20:11,750
100 taels.

213
00:20:19,620 --> 00:20:20,840
Your price is so high.

214
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:22,920
Fine.

215
00:20:23,520 --> 00:20:24,770
I have something here, too.

216
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:26,350
Just see whether you want to buy it.

217
00:20:27,650 --> 00:20:28,260
What is it?

218
00:20:31,020 --> 00:20:31,530
Your ear!

219
00:20:35,930 --> 00:20:36,520
Bastard!

220
00:20:41,410 --> 00:20:41,900
Li Wu.

221
00:20:42,420 --> 00:20:43,630
How dare you!

222
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:44,530
You want to rebel?

223
00:20:44,810 --> 00:20:45,710
You dare to hurt a Brocade-clad Guard?

224
00:20:47,380 --> 00:20:48,540
Killing a detective is nothing.

225
00:20:49,300 --> 00:20:50,440
We've even killed a deputy commander.

226
00:20:51,670 --> 00:20:53,470
You are really a rebel?

227
00:20:54,780 --> 00:20:55,790
Don't you have evidence?

228
00:20:58,970 --> 00:20:59,480
Lord Li,

229
00:20:59,900 --> 00:21:01,210
I have a big family to support.

230
00:21:01,550 --> 00:21:02,710
Please spare my life.

231
00:21:04,830 --> 00:21:07,120
How much are you going to pay for your ear?

232
00:21:07,950 --> 00:21:09,180
100 taels. 100 taels.

233
00:21:09,250 --> 00:21:09,860
100 taels?

234
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:11,410
Then we are even.

235
00:21:11,720 --> 00:21:12,940
We are even now.

236
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:15,740
Lord Li,

237
00:21:16,040 --> 00:21:17,320
I’m leaving now.

238
00:21:17,390 --> 00:21:18,200
I won't disturb you.

239
00:21:18,300 --> 00:21:18,840
Stop.

240
00:21:22,060 --> 00:21:23,830
How much are you going to pay

241
00:21:24,300 --> 00:21:25,290
to buy your ear?

242
00:21:28,340 --> 00:21:29,790
There's another ear.

243
00:21:57,350 --> 00:21:59,040
[Investigation Bureau]

244
00:22:18,520 --> 00:22:19,950
Lord Li, you're so kind.

245
00:22:20,310 --> 00:22:21,220
They are not here yet,

246
00:22:21,580 --> 00:22:22,930
and the gift is given first.

247
00:22:23,980 --> 00:22:25,030
This is not a gift.

248
00:22:25,790 --> 00:22:26,460
It's etiquette.

249
00:22:32,420 --> 00:22:33,350
Greetings, Chief Commander.

250
00:22:35,780 --> 00:22:36,720
So this is Li Dongfang?

251
00:22:38,080 --> 00:22:40,250
The sergeant transferred from the north?

252
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:41,890
Okay.

253
00:22:45,630 --> 00:22:48,540
Li Dongfang has just come to the bureau's office to report duty today,

254
00:22:49,330 --> 00:22:50,220
and you've already known each other?

255
00:22:51,470 --> 00:22:51,790
Yes.

256
00:22:54,740 --> 00:22:55,330
Li Dongfang.

257
00:22:56,080 --> 00:22:57,080
It's been a long journey.

258
00:22:57,760 --> 00:22:58,260
You must be tired.

259
00:23:00,910 --> 00:23:01,820
Are you hurt?

260
00:23:08,340 --> 00:23:08,840
My Lord,

261
00:23:09,770 --> 00:23:10,340
it's

262
00:23:11,020 --> 00:23:12,490
Officer Xie Kengran's blood.

263
00:23:13,850 --> 00:23:14,680
On my way here,

264
00:23:15,310 --> 00:23:16,880
I came across the Prince of Yan's spies, the Night Scouts.

265
00:23:17,690 --> 00:23:18,730
It was hard for me to fight with them alone.

266
00:23:18,750 --> 00:23:20,220
Luckily, Detective Xie helped me,

267
00:23:20,690 --> 00:23:21,930
and I managed to escape unscathed.

268
00:23:23,740 --> 00:23:24,200
However,

269
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:27,600
Detective Xie was killed by the Night Scouts,

270
00:23:29,380 --> 00:23:30,150
and died for fulfilling his duty.

271
00:23:33,950 --> 00:23:34,870
I have a question.

272
00:23:35,690 --> 00:23:36,210
Li Dongfang.

273
00:23:38,410 --> 00:23:39,080
You mean

274
00:23:39,700 --> 00:23:42,430
Xie Kengran was killed by the Night Scouts?

275
00:23:44,330 --> 00:23:45,470
I saw it with my own eyes.

276
00:23:49,220 --> 00:23:50,640
You've just arrived in the capital,

277
00:23:51,850 --> 00:23:54,450
and you may not know some things.

278
00:23:55,340 --> 00:23:57,530
Lu Zheng, the detective of the Investigation Bureau,

279
00:23:58,520 --> 00:23:59,920
has already signed the statement of confession,

280
00:24:00,610 --> 00:24:05,090
and admitted that he killed Xie Kengran and Wang Kegong.

281
00:24:05,770 --> 00:24:06,500
Wang Kegong

282
00:24:08,210 --> 00:24:09,540
was also killed by the Night Scouts.

283
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:12,390
The Night Scouts took Detective Lu's sword

284
00:24:12,860 --> 00:24:13,810
and killed Wang Kegong.

285
00:24:14,550 --> 00:24:16,120
I also saw it with my own eyes.

286
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:18,870
You've just been transferred to the capital from the north.

